            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer against demons, blacksmiths, and magicians who throw stones using the names of Biblical patriarchs and kings of 
                    kings of Israel and Judah, who are mentioned in the <term key="OldTestament">Old Testament</term> as ʾasmāt, i.e. 
                    <persName ref="PRS6357Lot"/> (indicated as <foreign xml:lang="gez">Lofḥam</foreign>),
                    <persName ref="PRS8925Solomon"/> and Jehoash (indicated as <foreign xml:lang="gez">Yoʾas</foreign>). Each of these 
                    names is repeated twice. A similar set of ʾasmāt derived from biblical names is present in a number of magic prayers, as for example: 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6853Prayer"/>, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6473PPAynaTela"/>,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT7366Bakama"/>, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT7367PPLaNahabt"/>,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT7063Devils"/> and <ref type="work" corresp="LIT7320Solomon"/>.</p>
            </abstract>
